---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the Museum of Civilization.">
  <div class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <header class="page-header">
        <p class="page-eyebrow">Curatorial Statement</p>
        <h1>About This Museum</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          In Emily St. John Mandel's novel <em>Station Eleven</em>, a traveling troupe of actors
          maintains a Museum of Civilization — a collection of objects from the world before
          the collapse. A smartphone. A credit card. Things that were once mundane, now artifacts.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is my version of that museum, assembled while civilization is still running.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each object here represents a moment when technology shifted — when something new
          entered the world and quietly changed how humans communicated, played, worked, or
          understood themselves. I lived through these shifts. I held these objects. I remember
          when they felt like the future.
        </p>
        <p>
          This archive is equal parts personal memoir and cultural record. The historical
          notes reflect why each object mattered broadly. The personal accounts reflect
          what they meant to me specifically.
        </p>
        <p>
          Civilization does not end all at once. It accumulates in objects like these.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <figure class="collection-panorama">
      <div class="panorama-frame">
        <img
          src="/images/Collection1.JPG"
          alt="The left half of the collection arranged on a shelf — AirPods, Kindle, Apple Watch, Nintendo cartridges, and the Tesla model."
          width="4949"
          height="2999"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/Collection2.JPG"
          alt="The right half of the collection arranged on a shelf — StarTAC phone, VHS cassette, Droid X, iPod nano, Game Boy, Xbox Kinect, and a floppy disk."
          width="5107"
          height="3100"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <figcaption>
        <span class="figcaption-eyebrow">The Collection, Assembled</span>
        The entire collection, laid out side by side on a shelf in my basement —
        the whole museum in one place before it was ever a website.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: 4rem var(--page-padding) 6rem;
  }

  .page-inner {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .prose em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* The collection diptych — breaks out wider than the text column */
  .collection-panorama {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 5rem auto 0;
  }

  .panorama-frame {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2px;
    background: var(--color-border);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .panorama-frame img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    transition: transform 0.6s ease;
  }

  .panorama-frame:hover img {
    transform: scale(1.03);
  }

  .collection-panorama figcaption {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .figcaption-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .panorama-frame {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
